Page 2 — Technical Mechanisms & Tensor/Flow Diagrams

⸻

Narrative Tensor Composition (NT)

The mathematical core enabling narrative-aware image synthesis.

The Narrative Tensor is a structured representation:

NT \in \mathbb{R}^{d_h \times d_c \times d_t}

Where:
	•	d_h — Hierarchical layers (character/world/symbol/emotion)
	•	d_c — Continuity constraints (identity, spatial locks, rules)
	•	d_t — Temporal features (story beat, Δtime, tension)

⸻

Diagram: Rank-3 Narrative Tensor

                       Narrative Tensor (NT)
                  Rank-3:  NT ∈ ℝ^{d_h × d_c × d_t}

                           d_h  (Hierarchical Layers)
                           ┌────────────────────────────────┐
                           │  Character Layer               │
                           │  World Layer                   │
                           │  Symbolic Layer                │
                           │  Emotional/Tonal Layer         │
                           └────────────────────────────────┘
                                    │
                                    ▼
                 ┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐
                 │                                            │
        d_c  →   │   Continuity Constraints                   │
                 │   (identity lock, spatial lock,            │
                 │    visual signature, rule constraints)     │
                 └────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                                    │
                                    ▼
                 ┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐
                 │                                            │
        d_t  →   │   Temporal Dimension                       │
                 │   (story beat, Δtime, tension,             │
                 │    causal dependencies, foreshadowing)     │
                 └────────────────────────────────────────────┘


⸻

Coherence Loop Flowchart

Mirror + Checksum enforce self-correcting narrative consistency.

                      ┌───────────────────────┐
                      │  Draft Image Output   │
                      └───────────┬───────────┘
                                  │
                                  ▼
                    ┌──────────────────────────┐
                    │ Mirror Coherence Audit   │
                    │ Checks: identity, logic, │
                    │ world consistency        │
                    └───────────┬──────────────┘
                                │
                     Pass?  ────┤────  Fail?
                                │
                                ▼
                         ┌──────────────┐
                         │  Checksum    │
                         │  Rule Set    │
                         │  Validation  │
                         └─────┬────────┘
                               │
                    All rules  │  Any rule
                     satisfied │  violated
                               │
                               ▼
                  ┌───────────────────────┐
                  │   ACCEPTED IMAGE      │
                  │(emit to user + update │
                  │      EchoFrame)       │
                  └───────────────────────┘
                               ▲
                               │
                               │  FAIL PATH
                               │
                     ┌──────────────────────────┐
                     │  Adjust Constraints       │
                     │  - tighten identity lock  │
                     │  - reinforce continuity   │
                     │  - emphasize temporal beat│
                     └───────────┬──────────────┘
                                 │
                                 ▼
                      ┌──────────────────────────┐
                      │ Re-generate with updated │
                      │    RenderSpec + NT       │
                      └───────────┬──────────────┘
                                  │
                                  └───→ back to Mirror Audit


⸻

Implementation Notes

No retraining required

NT and Daemon layers operate at inference-time, augmenting the orchestration layer.

Fast to prototype
	•	NTE can be built on a lightweight transformer
	•	Mirror/Checksum can use CLIP-like embeddings
	•	EchoFrame uses simple delta extraction

Compatible with Gemini’s architecture

Conditioning can be injected through existing cross-attention mechanisms.

⸻

Conclusion

The Narrative Tensor Architecture enables Gemini to move beyond single-frame artistry into story-consistent, cinematic-grade visual generation, unlocking entire new product categories.

This approach is modular, aligned with existing infrastructure, and grounded in mature research patterns (memory-augmented models, cross-attention conditioning, recurrent state machines).

A prototype could be built in 4–8 weeks, with full productization in a quarter.

